# Commit conventions

This project uses **semantic-release** (`@semantic-release/github`) with
**conventional commits** (`@commitlint/config-conventional`). Every commit
message must follow the format below so releases are automated and issues are
auto-closed when the PR merges.

## Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

<body>

<footer>
```

### Types (from `.releaserc.json`)

| Type | Release | When to use |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `fix` | patch | Bug fix |
| `feat` | minor | New feature / capability |
| `refactor(core-*)` | minor | Core module refactor |
| `perf` | patch | Performance improvement |
| `test` | patch | Adding / updating tests only |
| `docs` | patch | Documentation only |
| `chore` | patch | Build, CI, tooling |
| `*` (anything else) | patch | Catch-all |
| Any with `(no-release)` scope | **none** | Explicitly skip release |

### BREAKING CHANGE

Append `!` after type or add `BREAKING CHANGE:` in the footer → **major** release.

## Issue references — auto-close on merge

`@semantic-release/github` resolves issues listed with
[GitHub closing keywords](https://docs.github.com/en/issues/tracking-your-work-with-issues/using-issues/linking-a-pull-request-to-an-issue)
in the commit body or footer. **Every bug-fix commit must reference all related
issue numbers** (primary + duplicates from `docs/bugs/*.md`) so they auto-close
when the release publishes.

### Rules

1. **Footer** — Use `Closes #NNN` (or `Fixes #NNN`) for the primary issue.
   Add every deduped issue on the same line or subsequent lines:

   ```
   fix(pan): stop velocity from being disabled at scale <= 1

   The velocity calculation guard rejected all scales not strictly greater
   than 1, preventing inertia at the default zoom level.

   Closes #363
   Closes #433
   ```

2. **Multiple issues in one commit** — List each on its own `Closes` line.
   Do **not** comma-separate them (`Closes #1, #2` only closes #1 on some
   parsers).

3. **Feature requests** — Use `Closes` when the commit fully implements the
   request. Use `Ref #NNN` (no closing keyword) when partially addressed.

4. **Regression test commits** — Reference the issue but do **not** close it
   (the fix commit closes it):

   ```
   test(pan): add regression for velocity at scale <= 1

   Ref #363
   ```

5. **Scope** — Use the library area: `pan`, `zoom`, `pinch`, `bounds`,
   `controls`, `animation`, `css`, `build`, `api`, `minimap`.

## Examples

```
fix(zoom): fire onZoom callbacks from programmatic zoomIn/zoomOut

Programmatic methods now emit the same callback sequence as user-driven
gestures.

Closes #369
Closes #259
Closes #305
```

```
feat(controls): add directional pan buttons to Controls component

Closes #527
Closes #326
```

```
fix(build): include src/ in published package for source maps

Closes #529
Closes #542
```
